 Here's a simple JavaScript program that generates and prints out the ASCII and hexadecimal codes for characters from 0 to 7F.

```javascript
for (let i = 32; i <= 126; i++) {
    console.log(`ASCII: ${i} => Hex: ${i.toString(16)}`);
}
```
This program uses a for loop to iterate over the ASCII range from 32 (space) to 126 (~). For each iteration, it prints out the ASCII and hexadecimal codes of the current character. The `toString(16)` method is used to convert the character into its hexadecimal representation.
